  "text": "were able to estimate the prevalence of type 2 diabetes in children based on the indication for the prescriptions and found a high proportion of oral anti-diabetics used for PCOS [CITATION_1] . However, in our present study, not all databases record the indications for the prescription; hence, we were unable to estimate the prevalence of children receiving oral anti-diabetics for the treatment of type 2 diabetes. Consequently, some of our routine prescribing databases are less suitable for the assessment of type 2 diabetes.",
